# Release Metadata

Three files must stay in sync when preparing a release:

| File | What to update |
|---|---|
| `gradle.properties` | `pluginVersion` |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | New version section with date and categorized changes |
| `build.gradle.kts` | `changeNotes` (latest release highlights) and `description` (if the feature set changed) |

## Workflow

1. Bump `pluginVersion` in `gradle.properties`.
2. Add a new section to `CHANGELOG.md` following the existing Keep a Changelog format (`Added`, `Changed`, `Fixed`, `Security`).
3. Update `changeNotes` in `build.gradle.kts` → `intellijPlatform.pluginConfiguration` to match the new changelog entry as HTML.
4. If the release introduces or removes a user-facing feature, update `description` in the same block.

## changeNotes format

`changeNotes` is an HTML string rendered on the JetBrains Marketplace "What's New" panel. Use a `<h3>` for the version and a `<ul>` for bullet points:

```kotlin
changeNotes = """
    <h3>X.Y.Z</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Highlight one</li>
        <li>Highlight two</li>
    </ul>
""".trimIndent()
```

## description format

`description` is an HTML string rendered on the Marketplace plugin page. Keep it concise: a one-line summary, a `<ul>` of key features, and links to the project home and issue tracker.

## Reminders

- Always update all three files together; never bump the version without updating the changelog and change notes.
- See `RELEASING.md` for the full release checklist.
